Package fr.pyvain.websight.websight.PersonalDataGraph

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DataSet
    A class that represents the data carried by an edge or a vertex of a personal data graph, i.e. a set of URLs.
    Drawing
    This class represents a drawing of a graph.
    Edge
    A class that represents an edge of a personal data graph.
    Forest
    A data forest is a data structure based upon a personal data graph.
    InputGraph
    This class represents a general undirected graph.
    PolarCoords
    A class that represents radial coordinates.
    RadialLayout
    A radial layout is a style of graph drawing that places the vertices of the graph on concentric circles.
    Tree
    A data tree is a structure built upon a connected component of a data graph, which is composed of : a directed tree of vertices representing personal data of the user, which is defined by a set of vertices, a set of edges, a root, and a parent/children relation a set of additional edges, which are the edges of the connected component which are not in the tree Additionally, the number of descendants of each vertex is stored in the data tree, to fasten the computation of a radial layout of the underlying connected component of the graph.
    Vertex
    This class represents a vertex of a personal data graph.
